title: Highest HIV Prevalence
description: In 2022, Eswatini had the highest prevalence of HIV among the population aged 15-49, with 25.9% of this age group affected.

title: Highest Antiretroviral Therapy Coverage
description: In 2022, Eswatini achieved a 95% coverage rate for antiretroviral therapy among people living with HIV, one of the highest in the world.

title: Lowest Fisheries Production
description: Eswatini had one of the lowest fisheries production rates in 2022, with only 165 metric tons produced.

title: Highest Unemployment with Intermediate Education (Male)
description: In 2021, 77.067% of the male labor force with intermediate education in Eswatini was unemployed, the highest rate globally.

title: Highest Merchandise Exports to Sub-Saharan Africa
description: In 2023, 90.44% of Eswatini's merchandise exports were directed to low- and middle-income economies in Sub-Saharan Africa, the highest percentage globally.
